text: This week we are going to shine some light on forgotten women artists.Marianne North (1830–1890) was a biologist and botanical artist who painted during the Victorian era. She was trained as a vocalist, but her voice failed, and she then devoted herself to painting flowers. She travelled with her father a lot. He was a member of parliament and after he died she decided to continue travelling the world alone. She visited every continent, except Antarctica. Without the ease of photography, her work served, and still serves, as an important resource for studying the natural world. Various plants have been named in her honour, including an entire genus of plants named Northia.In London, you can see her work at Kew Gardens. #art #londonart #Londonartgallery #artmuseum #artdaily  #painting #londonartwalks #nejasartwalks #artinspiration #londra #londres #artist #tatebritain #tatemodern #visitlondon  #womenartists #womanartist #femaleartist #forgottenwomenartists #MarianneNorth #victorianart #britishart #botanicalart #drawings  #flowerpainting

text: “The Weather Project“, a gigantic art installation by Olafur Eliasson in Tate Modern, London in 2003. The Weather Project recreates the sun and the sky inside the Tate Modern’s Turbine Hall, using huge semi-circle mono frequency lamps hung from a mirrored ceiling which the reflection made look like a full circle. The experience is enhanced by fine mist made from a mixture of water and sugar in the air occupying the hall..Olafur Eliasson is a Danish-Icelandic conceptual artist known for his large scale art installation often in public space, utilizing elemental materials such as light, water, and air temperature to enhance the viewer’s experience especially the sensorial, movement, perception and the feeling of self..#olafureliasson #tatemodern #modernart

name: 2019-09-20 20.34.31 2137075476585704561_tatemodern.jpg
text: Accessibility Museums Accessibility to museums and their collections to those with special needs and all types of disabilities is a pursuit that is taken seriously by the majority of cultural institutions. The accommodations made for these audiences in the form of services and programs enhances the museum’s inclusiveness and thus increases a museum’s appeal. Although equality and inclusion are key goals, people with disabilities often report barriers in museums concerning physical accessibility and patronizing behaviors, misconceptions and stereotyping. Last month this topic went viral when Ciara O’Connor, writer for the Irish Sunday Independent newspaper, took to Twitter to express her frustration and anger after trying to access Olafur Eliasson’s steel plates installation “Your Spiral View” with her wheelchair in Tate Modern in London. The installation, part of Eliasson’s exhibition “In Real Life”, consists of an eight metre long tunnel through which visitors walk. The tunnel can only be reached via two steps. According to O’Connor, a friend of hers asked an attendant if a ramp was available, but the attendant became “immediately cross and weirdly defensive,” eventually telling her the lack of a ramp was “the curator’s choice” and to “go around the side.” When the tweets about the lack of wheelchair accessibility of the exhibition and the patronizing behavior of the attendant went viral, Tate released a statement saying they decided to include Your Spiral View as it was the only sculpture of its type in Eliasson’s body of work which could be loaned for exhibitions. They recognized it caused an access issue for wheelchair users, made an apology and pledged the comments would be taken on board in future decision-making. The row reinvigorated the debate about accessibility in museums, causing all sorts of questions. Do you think artists need to make sure in their designs that installations are accessible to everybody? On the other hand, doesn’t this limit their creative freedom? And should curators only choose to exhibit installations that are accessible to everybody? On the other hand, what if that means leaving out a key work in the career of an artist?

name: 2019-09-20 21.24.20 2137100550169149047_tatemodern.jpg
text: Niño que sobrevivió a tragedia en el Tate Modern se encuentra estableLa consternación y la incertidumbre reinaron en Londres cuando a principios de agosto en las inmediaciones de la Galería Tate Modern de Londres, se observó la presencia masiva de efectivos policiales, quienes acordonaron la zona con cintas de seguridad ante un incidente que se registró cuando un adolescente fue acusado de haber lanzado desde el piso 10 a un niño de 6 años de edad.A través de las redes sociales las personas se preguntaban qué estaba sucediendo en las inmediaciones de la galería, ya que el edificio emblemático en la orilla del río Támesis fue cerrado como resultado del incidente. Luego de transcurridas las horas, la Policía Metropolitana de Londres permitió que los visitantes fueran saliendo y la galería fue cerrada.El niño que sufrió de tan penosa tragedia, se encontraba con su familia visitando el edificio en calidad de turistas provenientes de Francia. Si mediar palabras, el adolescente de 17 años lo tomo y arrojó desde el piso 10.Afortunadamente el niño sobrevivió la caída y aunque se encuentra en condición crítica, se conoció a través de sus familiares que está haciendo grandes progresos y que es un luchador.Se realizó una campaña en Gofundme para recoger fondos que ayudaran a la familia a costear los gastos médicos. La respuesta fue masiva y más de 75 mil euros han sido recaudados para ayudar en la recuperación del pequeño.Más - Reino Unido | NoticiasFoto: PA#Noticias #ReinoUnido #actualidad #latinosenUk #españolesenUK #tatemodern #londres🇬🇧

text: Comes the tipping point in life, when we decide to a ‘stop and search’ and our emotional police bring us to a standstill. This allows us to scan all the little details in the spectrum of our being; scour all fuzzy or cryptic elements that are floating around in our mind and restore the fault lines in the cluttered tale of our life. ("The world was somewhere else")..... #floating, #tatemodern, #art, #photography

name: 2019-09-20 22.34.26 2137135834474556334_tatemodern.jpg
text: 'Continually In Space'#inspired by the planets in space I decided to create this piece using #acrylic paint. In the bottom right corner, behind my signature, you'll notice a silhouette. This is the hidden meaning behind this piece, about my obsession with viewing space, but also represents how I love to continually paint space. I find space relaxing and surreal, which is probably why I'm so obsessed with looking at it. Whenever the moon is out you can guarantee that I will be sitting at observing it.Stay tuned for part 2 and the final result.All work on this account may not be reproduced in any form without my permission.#dorsetartists #space #planet #painting #workinprogress #working #artstudent #art #artist #newartists #newartistspotlight #discover #discoverartists #tatemodern #winsorandnewton #artstalentz #artistoninstagram #artistwithautism #ArtistOnTwitter #artistsoftiktok #night #nightsky #inspiration #realistic #abstractart #dailyart #artoninstagram #artvideo

name: 2019-09-20 22.35.56 2137136589724682912_tatemodern.jpg
text: 런던 2일차 현재 2:35pm어제저녁 숙소에 도착 후, 짐을 대충 정리하고 씻고 누웠다. 나름 시차를 적응해보겠다고 버티고 버티다가 잠이 들었다.아침의 런던은 입김이 나올 정도의 기온이었는데 난 딱 좋았다 햇빛은 뜨겁고 바람은 찬기가 느껴지는...나와서 걷자마자 식료품점에 빵이 진열되어 있는 걸 보고 들어왔다 크로와상은 의외로 한국에서 보다 담백하고 깔끔했다.그렇게 먹고 일어나서 바로 버킹엄 궁전 근위병 교대식을 보러 갔다.(이상하게 오이스터 카드 살 때 두근거림)점심을 먹으러 버로우 마켓을 갔다. 쌀을 먹어야겠다 해서 유명하다는 빠에야 가게를 찾는데 시장이 너무 커서 길치는 그저 보이는 햄버거 가게에 줄을 서버렸다. (사고 나서 바로 보인 빠에야집) 하 한국에서도 안 먹는 햄버거를 이렇게 큰 걸... 결국 반을 남겼다.배불러서 걷다가 현대미술관인 테이트 모던에 와서 구경했다. 혼자서 전신샷을 찍을 수 있는 유일한 방법, 거울 셀카😂스벅에서 휴식 가지는 중_____또 어디 갈까

name: 2019-09-21 01.56.49 2137237695964214633_tatemodern.jpg
text: HUNG IN LONDONThe Three Dancers by Pablo Picasso 1925.Where to see: Tate Modern.Picasso started this painting as a realistic representation of ballet dancers rehearsing. While Picasso was working on it his old friend Ramon Pichot died. Picasso was reminded of events that happened twenty years earlier: Ramon Pichot and another friend Carlos Casagemas fell in love with the same woman, Germaine Gargallo. Carlos took his own life after shooting at Germaine. Recalling these events transformed Picasso’s approach. The distorted angular figures, harsh colours and thickly worked paint surfaces seem to express violent emotions. - Tate Modern, Gallery label, 2019...#art #london #artlondon #hunginlondon #painting  #artist #painter #pablo #picasso #tate #tatemodern #dancers

name: 2019-09-21 03.00.01 2137269511070203654_tatemodern.jpg
text: Nan Goldin (Washington D.C., 1953) ha documentado su vida y la vida de personas cercanas a ella desde 1970. Inmersa en la comunidad gay, transgénero y de drogas del barrio de Bowery en Nueva York, desarrolló una especie de diario de fotografías instantáneas de momentos íntimos  en el que mostró tensiones sexuales, soledad, enfermedad, pérdida, placer y felicidad. Ha recopilado estas fotografías en diferentes obras en numerosas ocasiones, entre estas "The Ballad of Sexual Dependency" (Balada de la dependencia sexual), 1981-96, la cual existe como un libro, una exposición y una serie de transparencias acompañadas por música.⠀⠀El museo Tate Modern de Londres muestra "The Ballad of Sexual Dependency" en una exposición que lleva el nombre de la artista hasta el 27 de octubre de 2019. ⠀.⠀.⠀.⠀@nangoldinstudio @tate #TheBalladOfSexualDependency #TateModern #London #NanGoldin #Photography #Art

name: 2019-09-21 03.03.47 2137271401015185110_tatemodern.jpg
text: BOAT-TRIP🚢⠀«О такой поездке ты ни за что не пожалеешь!»- посоветовал  мне @robin_sieger прокатиться на речном кораблике по Темзе. А сам отправился покорять горные маршруты Испании.⠀Речной транспорт может с успехом заменить #tube. Мы стартовали  от пристани North Greenvich, c того места, где находится канатная дорога cable cars🚡. Набережная очень красивая с широченными деревянными скамьями, на которых можно полежать на солнышке☀️ в ожидании своего кораблика.⠀Мы расположились на открытой палубе, чтобы наблюдать проплывающие мимо берега. Cначала миновали район небоскребов Canary Wharf, новый деловой центр🏙️, можно сказать, второй Сити.  А затем уже с нового ракурса любовались на знаменитые Tower Bridge и музей-крепость Tower of London.⠀Старинная церковь St. Paul`s. Мосты Millenium и London bridge. Небоскребы City. Галерея Tate Modern и другие достопримечательности...⠀Желтоватые волны Темзы бурлят за спиной от мотора корабля. Яркое солнце мешает снять красивый кадр. На качающейся палубе главное - не выронить телефон из рук.  На причалах запах дизельного топлива вмешивается в радостную атмосферу приключения, но нисколько её не портит.⠀Выходим с корабля на Embarkment. Раз сказал Robin выходить здесь, значит, так и надо. На противоположном берегу - колесо обозрения London Eye 🎡 словно ставит точку в речной прогулке.⠀Набережная утопает в чудесных английских садах🌺🥀🌹. А отсюда уже рукой подать до St. James Park, самого любимого в Лондоне🐿️🦢.⠀#london #londonlife #londonlifestyle #cityoflondon  #thames #towerbridge #towerbridgelondon #londontowerbridge #toweroflondon #canarywharf #canarywharflondon #cablecars #emirarescallecarsnight

name: 2019-09-21 03.26.50 2137283007625785977_tatemodern.jpg
text: It’s amazing what ends up being a nice surprise.  Here, a beautiful work I saw at #TateModern last night, by TAKIS, also known properly as,  Panayiotis Vassilakis.  Influential in the 1960s, his work now graces the Tate Modern until 27 October 2019.  This work uses electrical lights inspired by waiting for trains, evocative of the flashing lights and signals in the darkness.  Deep down, TAKIS was revealing energy but IMO, through a beautiful, Greek intellectual lens. “We have chased the sacred symbols and replaced them with electronic eyes”. I covet this work.#Takis #artgallery #artshow #londonlife #londonweekend #fridayfeeling #friyay #londonartscene #1960s #Tate #southbank #se1 #conceptofenergy #energy #greekartist #besurprised #goodshow

name: 2019-09-21 03.30.21 2137284768579382783_tatemodern.jpg
text: Did you know, when Tate Gallery was first opened on May 11, 2000, it became an instant sensation among the people in the United Kingdom? That year, it recorded 5.25 million visitors. When you visit London, one of the places you should never miss is the @tate. If you’re wondering what makes Tate Modern unique out of all the galleries in the world is that artworks are arranged in themes and not in chronology; Contemporary British artworks regarded as masterpieces live there; You can find works by Salvador Dali, Marcel Duchamp, Pablo Picasso, all under one roof and most importantly Tate Modern is free to enter. So don’t miss it out! Hope everyone having a great start to the weekend. Btw thanks to @chrisfredma for the great jump.

text: "ЭЙ МОСКВА МЫ ВЕЗЁМ ВАМ МК" "Маска – неотъемлемая составная карнавала. Гротеск. Бурлеск. Странное. Ужасное. Смешное. То, что способно удивлять и пробивать ту непроницаемую оболочку, в которую упаковало себя большинство современных людей. Маски не стесняются. Она (маска) не человек. Она притягивает и отталкивает, то есть разбалтывает стабильную уравновешенность стереотипа. Но в маске нужно уметь играть."Самая символически наполненная часть. Поэтому, с самым немногословным описанием программы.⠀ЧТО ВАС ЖДЁТ:⠀Теория:- Мировая культура маски⠀Практика:- Основные приемы оживления маски. Принципы создания персонажа. Маска и взаимодействие с публикой.⠀Бонус- Основы безопасности движения в контексте спонтанной нагрузки, восстановления после травм или длительной профессиональной деформации.⠀Ведущие:Олег Скотников - основатель театра, актёр, режиссёр, директор.Анна Шишкина - основатель театра, художественный руководитель театра.(P.s.на фото)⠀ ⠀МАСТЕР-КЛАСС "МАСКИ" МОСКВАКОГДА: 28-29 СЕНТЯБРЯГДЕ: Адрес: 2-й Кожуховский пр., дом 29к2ст16 МЦК ЗИЛ и метро Автозаводская, МоскваВО СКОЛЬКО:13:00-19:00СТОИМОСТЬ:  МК 5500р в день мероприятия 6000Регистрация в шапке профиля.

text: W1 Curates presents British abstract artist Ian Davenport..Ian Davenport is well known for his abstract paintings, which explore process and materiality. name: 2019-09-21 07.21.46 2137401248849019543_tatemodern.jpg
text: Privacy Or Visibility ...This might be the question being asked as you view the sculpture that is made up of over 500 Venetian plastic blinds by conceptual artist Haegue Yang. It hangs from the ceiling in one of the larger rooms and is part of ‘Materials and objects’ on display at the #tatemodern it’s huge and hard to photograph especially without people in the frame. I waited until the room cleared out, it was so quiet all you could hear were my footsteps as I approached the installation. I decided to use this close up so you could see the blinds Better and also because I was more connected to it the closer I got. As I watched the light change in every direction I found myself being pulled into it and wanted to share that experience....#haegueyang #conceptualart #beammeup #takemetoyourleader #materialsandobjects #privacyorvisibility #benetionblindsculpture #compresed #expanded #transparent #opaque #threedimensional #domesticitems #domesticbliss #londonartwalk #seemoreart #banksidemuseum #thetatemodern #framesoflondon #postcardsfromlondon #lovelylondon #mylondon

text: Ground control to major Tom...“Ten minute transmission 2003” by Jennifer Allora & Guillermo Cazadilla is part of #medianetworks it was inspired by artists like Alexander Calder and Vladimir Tatlins work. But I feel the presence of a third influential artist as I look at the shadows being cast from the sculpture made up of metal,nylon,radio transmitters & microphones making modern abstract wallpaper with their shadows. It reminds me of the first time I saw the sculpture & shadows made by Ruth Aiko Asawa’s lovely organic weightless wire worked sculptures. They still haunt me now in a good way. ..#tenminutetransmission2003 #jenniferallora #guillermocaldadilla #shadowplay #ilikeshadows #alexandercalder #vladimirtatlins #ruthasawa #ruthaikoasawa #modernsculptures #modernshadows #encrypteddata #orbit #medianetworks #tatemodern #thetatemodern #dayatthemuseum #seemoreart

text: I know I normally talk about theatre but Olafur Eliasson’s exhibition at Tate Modern is very theatrical. A dark room where a fountain is suddenly illuminated like an ice sculpture, another where a misty shower looks like here, a coloured fog where you can only see a few feet ahead, a room where the light is broken by a kaleidoscope, your coloured shadows interacting with others. It’s fun and magical but also making serious points about human society and the environment. #olafureliasson #tatemodern

name: 2019-09-21 17.00.01 2137692292457249171_tatemodern.jpg
text: #BORSCHинтересно​До 5 января 2020 в Tate Modern @tate проходит масштабная ретроспектива Олафура Элиассона @studioolafureliasso, где представлено 40 работ культового датско-исландского художника.​​Именно с Tate Modern началась всемирная слава Элиассона. Его инсталляция The Weather project (2003 г.) стала одной из самых посещаемых в истории современного искусства - посмотреть на нее пришли более 2 миллионов человек! Под потолком Турбинного зала Тейт был натянут отражающий экран и установлено 200 ламп, рассеивающих желтый закатный свет по наполненному туманом пространству. А в самой зрелищной работе сегодняшней выставки – Your Uncertain Shadow – на белой стене в магическом танце парят разноцветные тени посетителей.​​Свет вообще стал одним из ключевых элементов в творчестве художника.  Возможно, не будь в детстве Элиассона нефтяного кризиса 70-ых, когда каждый вечер в Исландии отключали электричество, ему не удалось бы прочувствовать в полной мере волшебное воздействие света на человека.Элиассон перевернул представление о том, что может стать объектом экспозиции. Благодаря ему в музейных залах появились настоящие радуги, реки, стены из мха, туман и даже огромное солнце. Элиассон окончил Королевскую датскую академию изобразительных искусств в Копенгагене. В начале карьеры переехал в Берлин, где основал собственную арт-студию. Работы Элиассона находятся в коллекциях крупнейших музеев современного искусства, включая Тейт Модерн (Лондон), MoMA (Нью-Йорк), Музей Гуггенхайма (Нью-Йорк), MOCA (Лос-Анджелес), и др.​​Olafur Eliasson Your Uncertain Shadow (2019)

name: 2019-09-21 17.14.38 2137699652764585994_tatemodern.jpg
text: The Edge of the Woods (c.1912).🎨 Painted by Charles Courtney Curran.Born: 13 February 1861, Hartford, United States.Died: 9 November 1942, New York, United States..📝 An Impressionist figure, genre, and landscape painter, Charles Curran is known as a prolific artist who created light-filled paintings, often of young women.Curran was born in Hartford, Kentucky, but in 1881 moved to Sandusky, Ohio.  After studying one year at the Cincinnati School of Design, he began a distinguished career when he moved to New York City in 1882 and enrolled in the National Academy of Design.  There he studied under Walter Satterlee.At age 23, he had his first public exhibition at the Academy and won numerous prizes from that time onward.  Five years later he received the Academy's Third Hallgarten Prize for "A Breezy Day", which was considered the most meritorious painting in oil.Following his training at the National Academy, he became a student at the Art Students' League.  He then studied at the Academie Julian in Paris from 1889 to 1891.  The French artist Jules Bastien-Lepage was a source of inspiration for Curran with his paintings of peasants as a common subject matter.From 1887 to 1935, he exhibited regularly at the Pennsylvania Academy.In 1903, artist Frederick Dellenbaugh invited Curran to Cragsmoor, an art center in the Hudson River Valley near Ellenville, New York.In 1910, Curran moved into a house there and established a studio. At this time, he turned to the themes and Impressionist style that would occupy most of the remaining 30 years of his life: young women in bright sunlight.  His female subjects are often elegantly dressed, posed, and feminine, with uncomplicated and dreamy gazes.  Curran later included flowered backgrounds in his paintings, a theme to last the remainder of his career.  He occasionally painted portraits and landscapes, as well as a series of views of the Imperial Temples of Peking.His works can be seen in collections at the Columbus Museum of Art in Ohio, the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York City, the National Gallery of Art in Washington, D.C., and the Toledo Museum of Art in Ohio..(Fig 2, 3, 4, 5: Details)...

name: 2019-09-21 18.11.57 2137728501908901188_tatemodern.jpg
text: Nam June Paik | Magnet TV | 1965 |Modified black-and-white television set and magnet |  An early example of Nam June Paik’s “prepared televisions,” Paik would alter the television image or its physical casing via the means of magnetism. The magnetic field interference would warp the television’s electronic signals, ultimately distorting the broadcasted image into an abstract form that changed when the magnet was moved. Radical in action, Paiks baseline concept undermined the seemingly inviolable power of broadcast television by transforming the TV set into a sculpture, one whose moving image was created by chance procedures and manipulated at will. Paik challenged the idea of the art object as a self-contained entity and established a process of instant feedback, in which the audiences direct actions had an effect on the form. Informing interactivity and allowing this idea to take momentum through the eyes and actions of the viewers - a similar framework of social media as we know it today. | #namjunepaik | #tatemodern | #archive

name: 2019-09-21 18.30.17 2137737726735208126_tatemodern.jpg
text: Mark Rothko's Seagram Murals from 1958 give one an idea of the artists struggle for a pure physical environment for his paintings. Originally commissioned for the Four Seasons in New York the paintings are now at the National Gallery of Art, Washington but were also a big part of the Rothko exhibition at the Tate in London. When focussing on creating a strong color experience it seems to me that men tend to work with rectangular shapes while women use round shapes and symbols. Rothko said that if nothing else works in painting, big and red would always be a good choice. Seeing these paintings it is hard to disagree. #heikedineguenther #corepainting #markrothko #seagrammurals #fourseanson #nationalgalleryofart #washington #tatemodern #london #deepred #powerofcolor #artistinspiration #modernmasterpiece

text: What a great way to recycle your broken cups and saucers! This was one of the many wonderful exhibits at @compton_verney gallery's summer exhibition 'A Tea Journey' which I went to see last weekend. From precious Japanese tea bowls to decorative silver tea urns used by the British aristocracy, the exhibition told a fascinating story of how tea drinking emerged in China and spread to Britain, driving its international trade and becoming a staple of British life in the 19th century. Thanks to the excellent guide for the tour, and to my dear friends including @linwell886 for coming with me all the way out to deepest Warwickshire for a spot of tea history and cake! #tea #teahistory #history #china #japan #museums #galleries #art #warwickshire #england #statelyhomes #highsociety #countrylife #teamad #obsessedwithtea #visitengland #daysoutuk #tate #tatemodern #porcelain #ceramics #uk #greatbritain #gb

name: 2019-09-21 18.43.28 2137744367224421119_tatemodern.jpg
text: Nam June Paik | 1963 | Zen for TV | During 1963 Paik created “Zen for TV”. The installation consisted of a television set turned on its side, in which Paik altered to display a singular vertical line. Evoking a stringed instrument, marrying Paiks dual career within composing music. Interestingly, two years on, Paik debuted “Magnet TV” (1965) an interactive sculpture that invited viewers to alter the television’s transmission by moving a large magnet across its exterior casing. | #namjunepaik | #tatemodern | #archive

name: 2019-09-21 21.20.43 2137823512398975660_tatemodern.jpg
text: HUNG IN LONDONThe Seagram Murals by Mark Rothko 1959.Where to see: Tate Modern.“I hope to ruin the appetite of every son of a bitch who ever eats in that room. If the restaurant would refuse to put up my murals, that would be the ultimate compliment. But they won’t. People can stand anything these days.” This series of paintings was originally commissioned by the Four Seasons restaurant in the Seagram Building, New York. Rothko was influenced by Michelangelo’s Laurentian Library in Florence, with its blind windows and deliberately oppressive atmosphere. Rothko commented that Michelangelo “achieved just the kind of feeling I’m after – he makes the viewers feel that they are trapped in a room where all the doors and windows are bricked up, so that all they can do is butt their heads forever against the wall.” After dining at the Four Seasons restaurant, Rothko, stunned by the prices of food claimed, “Anybody who will eat that kind of food for those kind of prices will never look at a painting of mine.” He resolved to reclaim his paintings and give back the commission money. The canvases went into storage; years later, after a series of lengthy negotiations with the Tate, he donated a number of them to the museum. .. - from https://www.artsy.net/article/artsy-editorial-why-one-meal-made-rothko-cancel-his-first-major-commission and the Tate Modern Gallery label 2019...#art #london #painting #artinlondon #hunginlondon #rothko #seagram #mural #tate #tatemodern #contemporaryart #artstories #story #painter #markrothko #michelangelo #artsy

text: CLOSE UPWho spotted the silhouette?'Continually In Space'#inspired by the planets in space I decided to create this piece using #acrylic paint. In the bottom right corner, behind my signature, you'll notice a silhouette. This is the hidden meaning behind this piece, about my obsession with viewing space, but also represents how I love to continually paint space. I find space relaxing and surreal, which is probably why I'm so obsessed with looking at it. Whenever the moon is out you can guarantee that I will be sitting at observing it.Stay tuned for part 2 and the final result.All work on this account may not be reproduced in any form without my permission.#dorsetartists #space #planet #painting #workinprogress  #artstudent #art #artist #newartists #newartistspotlight  #discoverartists #tatemodern #winsorandnewton  #artstalentz #artistoninstagram #artistwithautism #ArtistOnTwitter #artistsoftiktok #sky #night #nightsky #inspiration #realistic #abstractart #dailyart #artoninstagram

Ik had als kind een herbarium met geperste bloemen, heb een tijdje geleden opnieuw een klein collectie aangelegd als voorbeeld voor het aquarellen van blaadjes en ben benieuwd op welke manier je ze nog kan gebruiken. Een eerste blik in het boek leert me dat deze auteur de opties beperkt tot de manier waarop ze er zelf mee werkt, maar dat doet ze wel bijzonder mooi. Ze gebruikt geperste bloemen en bladeren als materiaal om Quiltachtige  werken mee te maken. Heel speciaal en inspirerend! #booklover #mieleest #boekenwurm #theartofpressedflowersandleaves #jennieashmore #bookstagram#instabooks #ireadbooks #instaread #boekstagram

name: 2019-09-22 03.23.26 2138006071292691466_tatemodern.jpg
text: Giorgio De ChiricoLa Malinconia della partenza1916Londra, TateGiorgio De ChiricoThe Melancholy of Departure1916London, TateDe Chirico created this painting after returning to Italy from Paris to join the Italian Army at the beginning of World War I. The Melancholy of Departure exemplifies his move away from the bright and open scenes of his earlier career, and his further focus on internal settings and abstract combinations of everyday items. It illustrates a cluster of items used in painting. An easel holds a map, and an archway in the back of the room reveals a tower in the background. This painting was also the inspiration for a song by American Jazz artists Mark Isham and Art Lande, also entitled The Melancholy of Departure.#giorgiodechirico#dechirico #lamalinconiadellapartenza #methaphyscis #contemporaryart #tatemodern #tatelondon #masterpiece #art #arthistory #melancholy #departure

text: YINKA SHONIBARE CBE - The British Library “Printed in gold on the spines of 2,700 of the books are the names of first or second-generation immigrants to Britain. Whether celebrated or lesser known, they have all made significant contributions to British culture and history. There are also books with the names of those who have opposed immigration. Other books are unmarked, suggesting that the story of immigration in Britain is still being written.” #art #books #tatemodern #yinkashonibare

name: 2019-09-22 04.40.50 2138045026662655378_tatemodern.jpg
text: London day 3.뒤늦게 정리하는 런던.출장 후 사흘을 연장했는데, 이날은 기사 마감하느라 오전 늦게 나왔다. 숙소 앞 테이트 모던 버스킹이 넘 좋아 한참을 서서 들었고, 세인트폴 대성당이 보이는 카페서 카푸치노를 마셨다. 괜히 밀레니엄브릿지도 건너고. 켄싱턴에 넘어가 3년 전 BBC PROM 공연을 봤던 로얄알버트홀에선 괜히 와인 한 잔..빡센 출장이 끝나고 여행이 시작됐단 생각에 매우 신날 줄 알았는데 막상 그렇지가 않았다. 날씨 때문인지 적당히 음울하고 적당히 좋았다. 계획 짤 여유도 없었고 몸도 피곤해 익숙한 곳 위주로 다녔다.런던에서 맛집은 기대도 안 하기에 점심저녁 모두 3년 전 가본 곳에 갔다. 한국에도 들어온 빌즈.. 예전엔 분명 스콘 맛집이었는데 별로였다. 에그베네딕트 뻑뻑해서 거의 남김. 저녁에 간 barrafina는 3년 전 완전 반해 두 번이나 갔던 곳. 맛이 없진 않았지만 그때만큼의 감동은 아니었다. 음식이 변한 건지 내가 좋은 걸 많이 경험해 웬만한 것엔 동하지 않게 된 건지 생각했다. 내일은 뭔가를 계획해야겠다 생각했다..#london #tatemodern #billslondon #millenniumbridge #royalalberthall #barrafina #fujixt20

text: Bit of a horrible quality but a Mondrian nevertheless 🙏🏼✨ • knowledge is power and awareness. I barely gave importance to art when I was living in London, and seeing this was so basic to me back then. I knew who Mondrian was due to my fashion history class but that’s it. So many art pieces that I’ve walked past without knowing their true value 😑 never stop learning guys, it gives everything you encounter much meaning.

text: ‘Silence’ oil on canvas, 80x120cm.‘The highest teaching in the world is silence. There is nothing higher than this. Silence is the ultimate reality. Everything exists in this world through silence. True silence really means going deep within yourself to that place where nothing is happening, where you transcend time and space. You go into a brand new dimension of nothingness. That's where all the power is. That's your real home. That's where you really belong, in deep Silence where there is no good and bad, no one trying to achieve anything. Just being, pure being.’ - Robert Adams.You Simply Are IIOriginals | Prints | Commissions.Paul Lock Solo Exhibition Tues 24 - Sun 29 Sept, 2019 Noho Showrooms, 67 Great Titchfield St, Fitzrovia, London.Private Viewing: Tues 24 Sept, 5pm to 9pm, RSVP & Press Release: Link in bio.Tuesday 12 - 5pm (PV 5 - 9pm)Wednesday 10 - 7pmThursday 10 - 7pmFriday 10 - 7pmSaturday 10 - 7pmSunday 11 - 5pm.———#paullockart #portraitpainting #portraitpainter #portraiture #portraitcommission #newpainting #newart #figurativepainting #figurativeart #art #commissionaportrait #maddoxgallery #artwork #painting #modernportraiture #modernart #artbasel #gallery #robertadams #newartist #halcyongalery #saatchiart #artforsale #prints #portraitgallery #tatemodern #abstractart #abstractpainting #contemporaryart #london

name: 2019-09-22 17.50.34 2138442513531200948_tatemodern.jpg
text: I want to speak LIFE over my city. So often I get tangled in the grind, complaining about the price of living, the smog, the relentless pace, the way you feel like the ground might open up and swallow you whole. I love this city; it’s my home, my heritage, my inspiration, my friend and my facilitator. London is full of opportunity, kind faces, friendly announcements on the underground, delicious cups of coffee, hidden streets, gloriously green parks, art that makes your heart stop, buskers that bring you joy, buildings that inspire courage, friends that are family, Grandparents that always have the door open, the Evening Standard magazine bringing you consistency, sunsets on the Southbank, free events from Time Out, flower markets, bookshops, benches that invite reflection, churches that display majesty and people who are pursuing something beyond themselves and doing their best to fight against the grain and make this city liveable, breathable and open to connection. Show me your London and I’ll show you mine and together we can thrive in its messy, fabulous milieu. Together we can forge the present chapter of London’s rich history.

text: ■ ■ ■ ■ ■Female Nudes are a signature of my Artworks, I was honored when the#CaliforniaAfricanAmericanMuseum exhibited nudes of #BillieHoliday and #Cleopatra, Female Nudes inspired by the #HarlemRenaissance and #Africa 🎨 🎨 ■ ■ ■ ■ ■This work is entitled BRAZEN LOVE,the Female is enraptured & emboldened by the prospects of LOVE, her eyes peer out from her breasts 🎨 🎨 ■ ■ ■BRAZEN LOVE is rendered in Sennelier Oil developed exclusively for #PabloPicasso in 1949, in 2014,I decided to use this medium in my oil paintings, the richness of the colors are unparalleled, I'm totally addicted. 🎨 🎨 ■ ■ ■MK 🎨 ARTIST 🎨 ■ ■ ■#FINEARTMICHAELKILGORE#GALLERIEMICHAELKILGORE#femalenudeart #femmefatale #pamgrier #marilynmonroe#matthewyokobosky #historyofart □ □ □ □ □#neoexpressionism #amadeomodigliani #tatemodern #hollywoodstarlet #fridakahlo#LucienFreud #AbstractFigurative #art #ARTBASEL #BROADMUSEUM #BROOKYLNMUSEUM #ARTNEWS #CENTREPOMPIDOU #MODERNART#GUGGENHEIM #juxtapoz

text: ‘Verb 2 Dip, Deep’. (‘Colours’ series, 2018)mixed media ‘COLOURS’ series is a comment on NUANCES of the language, AS WELL AS the nuance of ‘colours’...language can be equally USEFUL=USELESS...and I still, (steal) find it FUNDAMENTAL even if we all borrow the words we speak. ‘COLOURS’ is one of my comments on ‘THE ABSOLUTE POSSIBILITY OF DIS UNDERSTANDING’ which is not about ‘Misunderstanding’ it is about being understood in ways we do not really mean or maybe we do mean, ITS ABOUT THE CHANCE OF PLAYING finite and infinite GAMES. @artspace Reyzorro#contemporaryart#reyzorro @artspace #whitecubegallery #artnyc #moma#whitecube #whitechapelgallery #gagosian#themet #liquidskydsign#saatchigallery #miamibasel#serpentineuk #tatemodernmuseum #tatemodern #tatemodernlondon#haywardgallery #barbicancentre#pacegallery #artsy #londonartwalk #thefallmag#artmazemag#biennial#museumofmodernart #tatebritainmuseum #NewMediaArt #fashion #art#tategallery

text: I'd never heard of Brinco shoes (made by Judi Werthein) until today and the exhibition made me quite emosh. #brinco #tatemodern #artispolitical-Werthein had the Brinco trainers produced cheaply in China. Many global companies manufacture products in countries where labour is cheap and often poorly regulated. The artist hopes to draw attention to how easily goods move between countries, compared with the strict regulations around the movement of people. The same governments that allow the import of cheap goods from overseas often strictly control, and actively discourage, migrants from entering the country in search of better living conditions.

name: 2019-09-22 22.47.09 2138591788139395745_tatemodern.jpg
text: Just got back from a trip to Keble College, Oxford where my uncle, Vitit Muntarbhorn KBE, was selected to be part of an exhibition “Portrait of Keble” which marks the beginning of the 150th anniversary of the college. In 2016, Vitit Muntarbhorn was selected as the first UN Expert to protect LGBTQ 🏳️‍🌈 against violence and discrimination, setting a clear mandate to decriminalise same-sex relations globally. And with his previous positions as the UN Special Rapporteur on Human Rights in North Korea and as a member of UN Commissions of Inquiry covering Syria and the Ivory Coast, he was knighted for his contribution to International Human Rights in 2018. 28 individuals were selected from 40 years of co-education at Keble for their inspirational achievements, be they personal, professional, or both. My heart is filled with gratitude to attend this event. Dreams really do come true. 🙏 #WatchTheMuntarbhorns 🔥

name: 2019-09-23 00.45.03 2138651129781558902_tatemodern.jpg
text: Fancy eating a Kandinsky? Here is ‘Yellow-Red-Blue 1925’! A cake I designed and made for lovers of art. The brief was to set about designing a wedding cake not like the norm and so I designed a cake to be viewed from above to reveal one of their favourite paintings. It took on many forms from differing angles as you looked through the 3D cake shapes but the birdseye view revealed the amazing Kandinsky artwork. The cake was covered in @massa_ticino_sugarpaste, @saracinouk modelling paste and tempered isomalt @squireskitchen was used to create the 3D elements. Thank you goes out to @thecakeriebridgend for millions of help with baking and covering and Sharon for my isomalt lesson and borrowing of stuff and of course the bride and groom, Lisa and Jeff, for asking me as it was a privilege ❤️. . .#kandinsky #wassilykandinsky #kandinskyinspired #guggenheim #guggenheimmuseum #tatemodern #lenbachhaus #lenbachhausmünchen #centrepompidou #cakedecoratingmagazine #cakemasters #cake #edibleart #squireskitchen #fondant #massa_ticino_sugarpaste #art #weddingcakes #mrbakerscakes

name: 2019-09-23 00.52.57 2138655108454541035_tatemodern.jpg
text: How gorgeous does this jar look in the sunshine please? ☀️ 🌸 too sad there‘s no cabbage emoji. So I did a fermentation workshop with @soe_kitchen at @tate yesterday and turns out it’s ridiculously easy! I kept asking „when do we add the bacteria, where are the bacteria“ when, obviously, they were already on the veggies (can you believe I had an A in biology? Mistakes were made...). So LITERALLY all I did was:- Chopped some white cabbage, beetroot, ginger, and radish- Added sprinkles of cumin and fresh dill - Massaged everything in a bowl with 1-2 tbsp sea salt until that water was scrunched out - Put it in an air-tight jar.And now all I‘m going to do is wait! To get, I guess, a kind of sauerkraut? Stay tuned.----#tatemodern#olafureliasson#soekitchen#fermentation#fermentedfood#doityourself#doityourselffermentation#guthealth#probiotic#probiotics#healthyguthealthymind#lowcarb#cleaneating#cleaneats#foodishealth#biohacking#nutrition#healthyeating#foodprep#mealprep#glutenfree#healthylifestyle

text: One of my favourites from the William Blake exhibition. Not one of his more challenging pieces - it's Oberon, Titania and Puck with fairies dancing. It's a really well put together exhibition and worth seeing. A beautiful set of drawings from The Divine Comedy,Pilgrims Progress, more Shakespeare and lots and lots of biblical illustrations. One of the most poignant parts was the reconstruction of his first exhibition, which was derided in its time.#tatemodern #gallery #visitlondon #art #london #instaart #artgallery #artwork #exhibition #artofinstagram #WilliamBlake #williamblake #amidsummernightsdream

name: 2019-09-23 01.24.28 2138670968393052497_tatemodern.jpg
text: Niño Comiendo Sandía (c.1920).🎨 Painted by Joaquín Sorolla y Bastida.Born: 27 February 1863, Valencia, Spain.Died: 10 August 1923, Cercedilla, Spain..🖼 Oil on canvas 99,5 x 75 cm..📝 Cuando apenas contaba dos años de edad, fallecieron sus padres víctimas de una epidemia de cólera. Al quedar huérfanos fueron acogidos, su hermana Eugenia y él, por su tía Isabel, hermana de su madre, y su marido, de profesión cerrajero. Pasados los años, su tío intentó enseñarle, en vano, el oficio de la cerrajería advirtiendo pronto que su verdadera vocación era la pintura.Un viaje a París en 1894 lo puso en contacto con la pintura impresionista, lo que supuso una verdadera revolución en su estilo. Abandonó los temas anteriores y comenzó a pintar al aire libre, dejándose invadir por la luz y el color del Mediterráneo. Son precisamente las obras de colores claros y pincelada vigorosa que reproducen escenas a orillas del mar las que más se identifican con el arte de Sorolla.Sin embargo, fue un artista muy activo, que realizó también numerosos retratos de personalidades españolas y algunas obras de denuncia social bajo la influencia de su amigo Blasco Ibáñez.Su estilo agradable y fácil hizo que recibiera innumerables encargos, que le permitieron gozar de una desahogada posición social. Su fama rebasó las fronteras españolas para extenderse por toda Europa y Estados Unidos, donde expuso en varias ocasiones. De 1910 a 1920 pintó una serie de murales con temas regionales para la Hispanic Society of America de Nueva York.En el estilo más característico de Sorolla, el de técnica y concepción impresionista, destaca la representación de la figura humana (niños desnudos, mujeres con vestidos vaporosos) sobre un fondo de playa o de paisaje, donde los reflejos, las sombras, las transparencias, la intensidad de la luz y el color transfiguran la imagen y dan valor a temas en sí mismo intrascendentes.Algunos críticos consideran estas obras un cruce entre los impresionistas franceses y los acuarelistas ingleses. Existe una importante colección de pintura suya en el Museo Sorolla de Madrid..(Fig 2, 3, 4, 5: Details)...

text: GILBERT & GEORGE This is a poster from Gilbert And George's Show MAJOR EXHIBITION at London's World Famous TATE MODERN GALLERY in 2007.  This was their First Retrospective Exhibition and it was a sensation. It was signed by the Artist's in Silver marker Pen as the Artists wanted people to have an original work of art produced by them. Their slogan was Art for All. The Poster measures. 77cm x 51cm ( 30.5 ins x 20)Gilbert & George Major Exhibition Tate Modern: Exhibition 15 February – 7 May 2007. Gilbert & George place themselves, their thoughts and their feelings at the centre of their art, and almost all of the images they use are gathered within walking distance of their home in London’s East End. Framed and signed £100 Collection or £10 delivery: Hackney, Tower Hamlets, Islington, unfortunately no shipping#art #artist #artgallery #painting #artwork #artforsale #modernart #abstractart #gilbertandgeorge #tatemodern #tateposter

name: 2019-09-23 04.38.27 2138768597395467085_tatemodern.jpg
text: Yesterday was wonderful - wandering round London with no plans. It has been YEARS. I used to love weekends when I lived there, no responsibilities, no work as I was still teaching not a photographer yet, and lots of exploring. Got to admit I'm finding the new school run and routine all a bit stifling for me but it will just take some adjustment. I decided not to take my 'big' camera as I wanted to really connect with my husband but couldn't help shoot some images on my phone of course!.Making time for this is so good for the soul. Freedom to stop and watch and immerse..We left the kiddos with my parents and headed off to enjoy some time with no agenda. We started in #KingsCross, admiring the developments around #GranarySquare and #CoalDropsYard, it's been amazing to watch that area grow into something really social over the last decade, LOVE it. It was also #OpenHouseLondon weekend and we were lucky enough to be able to explore the old Victorian Waterpoint which contained a huge tank that filled the steam engines by the canal and railway..Then we crossed the river and had a little time on the Southbank in the sunshine before ducking into the Tate Modern to see the #olafureliasson exhibition :) I'm going to hop on to my stories with some more images of that and a little reflection if you are thinking of going! .I'm not going to let #sundaynightitis creep in this evening, am settling down to write the final session of the @bumblebee_collective photography day retreat I'm hosting next weekend - tickets are still available in my profile! We've had some super people book on over the weekend and it's not too late to join! Any questions pop them in my DMs! :) #photowalkKingsCross #Kingscrosscanal #openhouseLondon #TateModern #storiesoftheeveryday #igerslondon #Londonphotographer #streetphotographyKingsCross #alexaloyphotography

name: 2019-09-23 16.51.58 2139137798866703181_tatemodern.jpg
text: "There is never enough information for us to absorb or understand. We gather smatterings of the latest gossip about ideas such as the big bang or string theories. We are unable to wrestle with the depths of these concepts mainly because real comprehension of the mathematics is beyond us. But we are dreamers- we are fraught with wishful intuitions… Visual art, our media, is our way of acting out our intuitions it has always been my dream that just one of my intuitions would have some use or at least be related to real life" Charles O Perry.

text: This week we are continuing to shine some light on forgotten women artists.Marie-Gabrielle Capet (1761–1818) was a French Neoclassical painter.She came from a modest background and her previous background and artistic training are unknown, but in 1781 she became the pupil of the French painter Adelaide Labille-Guiard in Paris, one of the very few who had been accepted to the Royal Academy of Art. name: 2019-09-23 18.50.38 2139197519725318279_tatemodern.jpg
text: [Olafur Eliasson: In Real Life @ Tate Modern 1/7] 2003 年，Olafur Eliasson 在泰特現代美術館的渦輪大廳（Turbine Hall）放置了一個人造太陽，裝置吸引了超過 200 萬人次觀賞。藝術家把美術館最具標誌性的地方轉化成社交場所，塑造一個觀眾共同體驗的空間。16年後，這位在丹麥出生的冰島藝術家，又回到泰特與觀眾分享過去30年的創作。承接上一次的成功，展覽不只給予不同年齡層的觀眾另一場難忘的體驗，同時展示藝術家如何在創作上引發出當今最迫切的氣候問題。⁠⠀⁠⠀⁠------------⁠⠀⁠⠀© Olafur Eliasson 的《天氣計劃》（The Weather Project）。 圖片來源：泰特現代美術館網站，《天氣計劃》展覽 16/10/2003–21/03/2004⁠⠀------------⁠⠀⁠⠀⁠⠀#Tate #tatemodernlondon #tatemodern #Olafur Eliasson #Eliasson #ContemporaryArt #GlobalWarming #InstallationArt #architecturelovers #artlovers #artandnature #exhibition #review #museum #gallery #泰特 #去倫敦睇展覽 #泰特倫敦 #泰特倫敦美術館 #英國展覽 #展覽 #藝術 #當代藝術 #香港人在倫敦 #博物館里數 #博物館 #美術館 ⁠#裝置藝術

text: ‘Maman’ (Spider), 1994, a giant bronze and granite sculpture of an arachnid, one of the first of several spiders created by Louise Bourgeois. It was first made for the opening of Tate Modern in May 2000 as part of a Bourgeois’s commission for the Turbine Hall, the grand central space of the museum. Thirty feet high and more than 30 feet wide, the spider became one of the largest sculptures in the world and several versions were later cast in Bronze, many which were then placed on permanent display....#thewomanartist #louisebourgeois #artist #artwork #artoftheday #instagram #painting #acrylic #oil #london #sculpture #curator #beirut #spain #contemporary #contemporaryart #pastecolors #brushstrokes #art #newyork #france #paris #spider #woman #wood #pigment #contemporaryart #tatemodern #tate #spider

name: 2019-09-23 20.59.23 2139262324591374416_tatemodern.jpg
text: _10월 그림 읽는 모임의 테마로 로스코의 색면추상을 선정했다. 마침 그에 맞춰 원대표님께서 런던으로 여행을 가셨다. “대표님! 테이트 모던에 있는 로스코 룸 꼬옥 가보셔야 해유!” 강력 추천(을 가장한 부탁)을 드렸다. 그렇게 원대표님께서 로스코  룸에 가셔서 멋지게 사진도 찍어서 보내주셨다. 실제로는 훨씬 어둡고 또 고요한 곳이다. 사진에서도 로스코 룸의 낮고 무거운, 그러나 압도적인 분위기가 느껴지는 것 같다. 10월 그림 읽는 독서모임에서 만날 곳은 테이트 모던의 로스코 룸도 휴스턴의 로스코 채플도 아닌, 서울의 리움 미술관이다. 작품 수는 단 2점 뿐이지만, 서울에서 상설전시로 로스코 작품을 볼 수 있다는 것만으로도 감사할 따름이다. 특히 불교미술 전시실에 자코메티 조각과 불상과 나란히 놓여있는 로스코의 작품은 몰입을 위한 분위기를 선사하기에 더할 나위 없을 것이라 기대한다.-#그림읽는독서모임#하나의책 #독서모임 #전시모임 #그림모임#마크로스코 #로스코 #markrothko #rothko #테이트모던 #tatemodern #리움 #leeum

name: 2019-09-23 22.29.27 2139307649699464672_tatemodern.jpg
text: #hART ♥️“A friend is someone who knows all about you and still loves you.Memories of your childhood come back and are so clear and vivid it’s like being young again__Colours seem brighter and more brilliant. Laughter seems part of daily life. A phone call or two during the day helps to get you through a long day’s work and always brings a smile to your face. In their presence, there’s no need for continuous conversation, but you find you’re quite content in just having them nearby. You find strength in knowing you have a true friend and possibly a soul mate who will remain loyal to the end, knowing that they are a part of your life.” ❤️ #live #lough #love #respect 🙏#tatemodernmuseum #art #heart #tatemodern #museums  #explore #london #igger #instagram #instamood #instaday #ootdfashion #ootd #blackfriarsbridge 📍

name: 2019-09-24 00.32.07 2139369394701554641_tatemodern.jpg
text: Если будете в Лондоне, обязательно загляните в Галерею Тейт Модерн, открытую в 2000 году. Размещается она в здании бывшей гидроэлектростанции и содержит коллекции XX века и современного искусства со всего мира. В выставочных залах можно увидеть произведения Пикассо, Матисса, Сезанна, Поллока, Ротко, Уорхола и многих других. Причем картины сгруппированы скорее тематически, чем хронологически. Вход в галерею бесплатный за исключением тех дней, когда здесь проводят масштабные и нашумевшие выставки⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀#Tate #london #england #gallery #tatemodern #лондон галерея #галереятейт #путешествие #искусство #живопись #культура

name: 2019-09-24 00.42.55 2139374831962055928_tatemodern.jpg
text: A Young Girl in Profile (c.1881).🎨 Painted by William-Adolphe Bouguereau.Born: 30 November 1825, La Rochelle, France.Died: 19 August 1905, La Rochelle, France. (aged 79).🖼 Oil on canvas 40 x 33 cm..📝 His work was characterized by a highly finished, technically impeccable realism and a sentimental interpretation of his subject matter.Bouguereau received many honours in the 1860s and ’70s and became for a time the most famous French painter of his day.In his later years he decorated the chapels of several Parisian churches and painted religious compositions in a Pre-Raphaelite style.Throughout the course of his life, Bouguereau executed 822 known finished paintings, although the whereabouts of many are still unknown..(Fig 2, 3, 4: Details).....#museum #moma #metmuseum #museedulouvre #britishmuseum #nationalgallery #museodelprado #vangoghmuseum #brooklynmuseum #artforum #artbasel #tatemodern #instamuseum #rijksmuseum #whitneymuseum #nationalgalleryofvictoria #nationalmuseum #gettymuseum #curator #graffiti #streetart #oilpainting #realism #williamadolphebouguereau #larochelle #france #yourarttimes

text: Tate Modern... Never fails to impress!!.Checking out some old favourites like Rothko, Schad, Frampton and also Lichtenstein's original "Whaam!!" of which I have an original limited edition lithograph produced by this gallery in 1967, in the Belle Epoque Collection... 😍.Even more exciting was artists I learnt about including Ibrahim El-Salahi, Saloua Raouda Choucair, Tsuyoshi Maekawa, Evelyne Axell, Helio Oiticica and Jeram Patel... So inspiring!!🥰.#newyork #expressionist #abstract #abstractart #abstractexpressionism #pop #popart #dutch #dutchart #stedelijkmuseum #abstraction #tatemodern #london #rothko #modernart #modernism #modernist #postexpressionism #amsterdam #tate #lichtenstein #europe #europeanart #sydney #melbourne #artforsale #kunst

name: 2019-09-24 01.57.00 2139412115583440942_tatemodern.jpg
text: I am having a love affair with life💕•If I’ve learned anything worthwhile in life it is this: there is nothing more important than FEELING GOOD and enjoying life to the MAX!•We create with our energy. What determines our energy is our feelings. •Traveling and doing things I love creates passionate and inspires feelings for me that cause me to dream bigger and feel so good!•I am discovering my reality mirrors my fantasies, because I feel good most of the time. I’m constantly looking for ways to feel and provoke even more goodness in my life!•London completely whisked me away into the dreamland where I feel SO freaking GOOD!💕•••#elleleva #loa #feelinggood #londonbeauty #lifecoach #masterofmylife #creatorofmydreams #thisisheaven #soinlove #lovemylife #pdxlifecoach #heavenismyreality #bestlife #tatemodern #harrodbeauty #gratitude #sograteful

name: 2019-09-24 05.47.52 2139528318733920257_tatemodern.jpg
text: #212 Olafur Eliasson jóideje kedvencem, izlandi születésű, most 52 éves művész, akinek elképesztően jó munkái vannak, amikben a fénynek, tükröződéseinek, a világosságnak nagy szerepe van. Egyrészt olyanokat csinál, amit élmény nézni, megtapasztalni; átbújni fénykapukon, százezer szikrázó kis pászmát figyelni, amint szétolvadnak egy klasszicista palota termében, arany fényfolyosókat teremt, ezüstben csillogó járatokat. Magadat is megéled közben, a többi embert, aki veled részt vesz az élményben, és egyre nagyobb hangsúlyt kapnak a világ nagy dimenzió. 2003-ban a Tate-ben a Napot imitálta: több, mint kétmillióan - Budapest lakossága!! - mentek el a múzeumba, hogy megtapasztalják a The Weather Project pszichedelikus sárga áradását, a ködöt, ami apró felhőkké állt össze. Tavaly, szövetkezve egy tudóssal, több tonnányi jeget hoztak el Grönlandról London belvárosába, egy klímacsúcshoz időzítve az akciót, hogy eléggé kézzelfoghatóvá váljon, nincs idő, ezek a tömbök olvadnak, Londonban nyilván, de eredeti helyükön is. Ma olvasom, hogy az ENSZ kreált egy tisztséget, és rögtön felkérte őt, szóval mától ez a mega-ismert, tömegeket mozgósítani képes, népszerű, okos, kreatív férfi a Klímaügy Jószolgálati Nagykövete. Szuper, mennyire értelmes dolog. Bravo, bravo, bravo. #eszembejutotterrôlegykép #mindennapraegymû #212 #olafureliasson #szupercsávó #theweatherproject #2003 #goodwillambassador #climatechange #climatechangeisreal #tatemodern #turbinehall

name: 2019-09-24 09.38.06 2139644197884373889_tatemodern.jpg
text: ‘Verb 2 Plant, Plant’. (‘Colours’ series, 2018)‘COLOURS’ series is a comment on NUANCES of the language, AS WELL AS the nuance of ‘colours’...language can be equally USEFUL=USELESS...and I still, (steal) find it FUNDAMENTAL even if we all borrow the words we speak. ‘COLOURS’ is one of my comments on ‘THE ABSOLUTE POSSIBILITY OF DIS UNDERSTANDING’ which is not about ‘Misunderstanding’ it is about being understood in ways we do not really mean or maybe we do mean, ITS ABOUT THE CHANCE OF PLAYING finite and infinite GAMES. @artspace Reyzorro#contemporaryart#reyzorro @artspace #whitecubegallery #artnyc #moma#whitecube #whitechapelgallery #gagosian#themet #liquidskydsign#saatchigallery #miamibasel#serpentineuk #tatemodernmuseum #tatemodern #tatemodernlondon#haywardgallery #barbicancentre#pacegallery #artsy #londonartwalk #thefallmag#artmazemag#biennial#museumofmodernart #tatebritainmuseum #NewMediaArt #fashion #art#tategallery

text: I have to admit I am a bit late to the party on this! What’s new hey? On Saturday I popped back into Tate Modern (one of my favourite places, for those not so regular viewers 😂) and finally headed to this amazing piece, made from Venetian window blinds. I hope the artist Haegue Yang, doesn’t mind my reimagined vision of it through my edit. .———————————————————————Title: Sol LeWitt Upside Down – Structure with Three Towers, Expanded 23 Times, Split in Three.———————————————————————.#haegueyang #tatemodern #tate #londongalleries #sculpture #reimagined #nikon #lightroom #geometry #futuristic #windowblinds #venetianblinds #artwork #masterpieces #ig_masterpiece #thisisart #thisissculpture #londondestination #londondisclosure #igerslondon #instaart #reworked #lighting #light #hue #lo_allthingslondon #design #explorelondon #londonvibes
